{
  "texts": [
    "Application of strong duality D ⋆ = P ⋆ and optimality of P ⋆ ≥ P ⋆ p to Theorem 1 leads toD ⋆ p -P ⋆ ≤ (M + β + M ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1) ν.",
    "On the other hand, P ⋆ -D ⋆ p = D ⋆ -D ⋆ p ≤ D(λ ⋆ p) -D p (λ ⋆ p) ≤ (M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1)ν where the first inequality is due to D ⋆ = D(λ ⋆) ≤ D(λ ⋆ p), and the last inequality is an application of Lemma 3 with λ = λ ⋆ p. B.5 Proof of Lemma 4Proof.",
    "According Assumption 5,D(λ) ≥ D(λ ⋆) + ∇D(λ ⋆) ⊤ (λ -λ ⋆) + µ ⋆ D 2 ∥λ -λ ⋆ ∥ 2 = D(λ ⋆) + E x E y ∼ π ⋆ (• | x) [ h(x, y)] ⊤ (λ -λ ⋆) + µ ⋆ D 2 ∥λ -λ ⋆ ∥ 2where the equality is due to Danskin's theorem.",
    "We note the complementary slackness condition:E x E y ∼ π ⋆ (• | x) [ h(x, y)] ⊤ λ ⋆ = 0and the feasibility conditionE x E y ∼ π ⋆ (• | x) [ h(x, y)] ≥ 0.",
    "Hence, D(λ) ≥ D(λ ⋆) + µ ⋆ D 2 ∥λ -λ ⋆ ∥ 2."
